{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"We're 25, 26 years after"},{"time":2000,"text":"the advent of the Macintosh,"},{"time":4000,"text":"which was an astoundingly seminal event"},{"time":6000,"text":"in the history"},{"time":8000,"text":"of human-machine interface"},{"time":10000,"text":"and in computation in general."},{"time":12000,"text":"It fundamentally changed the way"},{"time":14000,"text":"that people thought about computation,"},{"time":16000,"text":"thought about computers,"},{"time":18000,"text":"how they used them and who and how many people were able to use them."},{"time":21000,"text":"It was such a radical change, in fact,"},{"time":23000,"text":"that the early Macintosh development team"},{"time":25000,"text":"in '82, '83, '84"},{"time":27000,"text":"had to write an entirely new operating system from the ground up."},{"time":30000,"text":"Now, this is an interesting little message,"},{"time":32000,"text":"and it's a lesson that has since, I think,"},{"time":34000,"text":"been forgotten or lost or something,"},{"time":36000,"text":"and that is, namely, that the OS is the interface."},{"time":39000,"text":"The interface is the OS."},{"time":41000,"text":"It's like the land and the king (i.e. Arthur) they're inseparable, they are one."},{"time":44000,"text":"And to write a new operating system was not a capricious matter."},{"time":47000,"text":"It wasn't just a matter of tuning up some graphics routines."},{"time":50000,"text":"There were no graphics routines. There were no mouse drivers."},{"time":53000,"text":"So it was a necessity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55000,"text":"But in the quarter-century since then,"},{"time":57000,"text":"we've seen all of the fundamental"},{"time":59000,"text":"supporting technologies go berserk."},{"time":61000,"text":"So memory capacity and disk capacity"},{"time":64000,"text":"have been multiplied by something between 10,000 and a million."},{"time":67000,"text":"Same thing for processor speeds."},{"time":69000,"text":"Networks, we didn't have networks at all"},{"time":71000,"text":"at the time of the Macintosh's introduction,"},{"time":74000,"text":"and that has become the single most salient aspect"},{"time":76000,"text":"of how we live with computers."},{"time":78000,"text":"And, of course, graphics: Today"},{"time":80000,"text":"84 dollars and 97 cents at Best Buy"},{"time":83000,"text":"buys you more graphics power"},{"time":85000,"text":"than you could have gotten for a million bucks from SGI only a decade ago."},{"time":88000,"text":"So we've got that incredible ramp-up."},{"time":90000,"text":"Then, on the side, we've got the Web"},{"time":92000,"text":"and, increasingly, the cloud,"},{"time":94000,"text":"which is fantastic,"},{"time":96000,"text":"but also -- in the regard in which an interface is fundamental --"},{"time":99000,"text":"kind of a distraction."},{"time":101000,"text":"So we've forgotten to invent new interfaces."},{"time":103000,"text":"Certainly we've seen in recent years a lot of change in that regard,"},{"time":105000,"text":"and people are starting to wake up about that."},{"time":109000,"text":"So what happens next? Where do we go from there?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":111000,"text":"The problem, as we see it,"},{"time":113000,"text":"has to do with a single, simple word: \"space,\""},{"time":115000,"text":"or a single, simple phrase:"},{"time":117000,"text":"\"real world geometry.\""},{"time":119000,"text":"Computers and the programming languages"},{"time":121000,"text":"that we talk to them in, that we teach them in,"},{"time":123000,"text":"are hideously insensate when it comes to space."},{"time":126000,"text":"They don't understand real world space."},{"time":128000,"text":"It's a funny thing because the rest of us occupy it quite frequently and quite well."},{"time":131000,"text":"They also don't understand time, but that's a matter for a separate talk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":134000,"text":"So what happens if you start to"},{"time":136000,"text":"explain space to them?"},{"time":141000,"text":"One thing you might get is something like the Luminous Room."},{"time":144000,"text":"The Luminous Room is a system"},{"time":146000,"text":"in which it's considered that"},{"time":148000,"text":"input and output spaces are co-located."},{"time":150000,"text":"That's a strangely simple,"},{"time":152000,"text":"and yet unexplored idea, right?"},{"time":154000,"text":"When you use a mouse, your hand is down here on the mouse pad."},{"time":157000,"text":"It's not even on the same plane as what you're talking about:"},{"time":159000,"text":"The pixels are up on the display."},{"time":161000,"text":"So here was a room in which all the walls, floors, ceilings,"},{"time":164000,"text":"pets, potted plants, whatever was in there,"},{"time":166000,"text":"were capable, not only of display but of sensing as well."},{"time":169000,"text":"And that means input and output are in the same space"},{"time":171000,"text":"enabling stuff like this."},{"time":173000,"text":"That's a digital storage in a physical container."},{"time":175000,"text":"The contract is the same"},{"time":177000,"text":"as with real word objects in real world containers."},{"time":180000,"text":"Has to come back out, whatever you put in."},{"time":183000,"text":"This little design experiment"},{"time":185000,"text":"that was a small office here knew a few other tricks as well."},{"time":188000,"text":"If you presented it with a chess board,"},{"time":190000,"text":"it tried to figure out what you might mean by that."},{"time":192000,"text":"And if there was nothing for them to do,"},{"time":194000,"text":"the chess pieces eventually got bored"},{"time":196000,"text":"and hopped away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":198000,"text":"The academics who were overseeing this work"},{"time":201000,"text":"thought that that was too frivolous,"},{"time":203000,"text":"so we built deadly serious applications"},{"time":205000,"text":"like this optics prototyping workbench"},{"time":207000,"text":"in which a toothpaste cap on a cardboard box"},{"time":210000,"text":"becomes a laser."},{"time":212000,"text":"The beam splitters and lenses are represented by physical objects,"},{"time":215000,"text":"and the system projects down the laser beam path."},{"time":218000,"text":"So you've got an interface that has no interface."},{"time":220000,"text":"You operate the world as you operate the real world,"},{"time":223000,"text":"which is to say, with your hands."},{"time":225000,"text":"Similarly, a digital wind tunnel with digital wind"},{"time":227000,"text":"flowing from right to left --"},{"time":229000,"text":"not that remarkable in a sense; we didn't invent the mathematics."},{"time":232000,"text":"But if you displayed that on a CRT or flat panel display,"},{"time":234000,"text":"it would be meaningless to hold up an arbitrary object,"},{"time":237000,"text":"a real world object in that."},{"time":239000,"text":"Here, the real world merges with the simulation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243000,"text":"And finally, to pull out all the stops,"},{"time":245000,"text":"this is a system called Urp, for urban planners,"},{"time":248000,"text":"in which we give architects and urban planners back"},{"time":251000,"text":"the models that we confiscated"},{"time":253000,"text":"when we insisted that they use CAD systems."},{"time":255000,"text":"And we make the machine meet them half way."},{"time":257000,"text":"It projects down digital shadows, as you see here."},{"time":260000,"text":"And if you introduce tools like this inverse clock,"},{"time":263000,"text":"then you can control the sun's position in the sky."},{"time":265000,"text":"That's 8 a.m. shadows."},{"time":267000,"text":"They get a little shorter at 9 a.m."},{"time":269000,"text":"There you are, swinging the sun around."},{"time":271000,"text":"Short shadows at noon and so forth."},{"time":275000,"text":"And we built up a series of tools like this."},{"time":278000,"text":"There are inter-shadowing studies"},{"time":280000,"text":"that children can operate,"},{"time":282000,"text":"even though they don't know anything about urban planning:"},{"time":284000,"text":"To move a building, you simply reach out your hand and you move the building."},{"time":287000,"text":"A material wand makes the building"},{"time":289000,"text":"into a sort of Frank Gehry thing that reflects light in all directions."},{"time":292000,"text":"Are you blinding passers by and motorists on the freeways?"},{"time":295000,"text":"A zoning tool connects distant structures, a building and a roadway."},{"time":298000,"text":"Are you going to get sued by the zoning commission? And so forth."},{"time":302000,"text":"Now, if these ideas seem familiar"},{"time":304000,"text":"or perhaps even a little dated,"},{"time":306000,"text":"that's great; they should seem familiar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":308000,"text":"This work is 15 years old."},{"time":311000,"text":"This stuff was undertaken at MIT and the Media Lab"},{"time":314000,"text":"under the incredible direction of Professor Hiroshi Ishii,"},{"time":317000,"text":"director of the Tangible Media Group."},{"time":319000,"text":"But it was that work that was seen"},{"time":321000,"text":"by Alex McDowell,"},{"time":323000,"text":"one of the world's legendary production designers."},{"time":326000,"text":"But Alex was preparing a little, sort of obscure, indie, arthouse film"},{"time":329000,"text":"called \"Minority Report\" for Steven Spielberg,"},{"time":332000,"text":"and invited us to come out from MIT"},{"time":334000,"text":"and design the interfaces"},{"time":337000,"text":"that would appear in that film."},{"time":340000,"text":"And the great thing about it was"},{"time":342000,"text":"that Alex was so dedicated to the idea of verisimilitude,"},{"time":345000,"text":"the idea that the putative 2054"},{"time":348000,"text":"that we were painting in the film be believable,"},{"time":351000,"text":"that he allowed us to take on that design work"},{"time":353000,"text":"as if it were an R&amp;D effort."},{"time":355000,"text":"And the result is sort of"},{"time":357000,"text":"gratifyingly perpetual."},{"time":359000,"text":"People still reference those sequences in \"Minority Report\""},{"time":362000,"text":"when they talk about new UI design."},{"time":364000,"text":"So this led full circle, in a strange way,"},{"time":366000,"text":"to build these ideas into what we believe"},{"time":369000,"text":"is the necessary future of human machine interface:"},{"time":372000,"text":"the Spatial Operating Environment, we call it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":377000,"text":"So here we have a bunch of stuff, some images."},{"time":380000,"text":"And, using a hand,"},{"time":382000,"text":"we can actually exercise six degrees of freedom,"},{"time":385000,"text":"six degrees of navigational control."},{"time":388000,"text":"And it's fun to fly through Mr. Beckett's eye."},{"time":390000,"text":"And you can come back out"},{"time":392000,"text":"through the scary orangutan."},{"time":394000,"text":"And that's all well and good."},{"time":397000,"text":"Let's do something a little more difficult."},{"time":400000,"text":"Here, we have a whole bunch of disparate images."},{"time":402000,"text":"We can fly around them."},{"time":404000,"text":"So navigation is a fundamental issue."},{"time":406000,"text":"You have to be able to navigate in 3D."},{"time":409000,"text":"Much of what we want computers to help us with in the first place"},{"time":412000,"text":"is inherently spatial."},{"time":414000,"text":"And the part that isn't spatial can often be spatialized"},{"time":416000,"text":"to allow our wetware to make greater sense of it."},{"time":419000,"text":"Now we can distribute this stuff in many different ways."},{"time":422000,"text":"So we can throw it out like that. Let's reset it."},{"time":424000,"text":"We can organize it this way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426000,"text":"And, of course, it's not just about navigation,"},{"time":429000,"text":"but about manipulation as well."},{"time":431000,"text":"So if we don't like stuff,"},{"time":433000,"text":"or we're intensely curious about"},{"time":435000,"text":"Ernst Haeckel's scientific falsifications,"},{"time":438000,"text":"we can pull them out like that."},{"time":440000,"text":"And then if it's time for analysis, we can pull back a little bit"},{"time":443000,"text":"and ask for a different distribution."},{"time":448000,"text":"Let's just come down a bit"},{"time":451000,"text":"and fly around."},{"time":454000,"text":"So that's a different way to look at stuff."},{"time":457000,"text":"If you're of a more analytical nature"},{"time":459000,"text":"then you might want, actually, to look at this"},{"time":461000,"text":"as a color histogram."},{"time":464000,"text":"So now we've got the stuff color-sorted,"},{"time":467000,"text":"angle maps onto color."},{"time":470000,"text":"And now, if we want to select stuff,"},{"time":472000,"text":"3D, space,"},{"time":474000,"text":"the idea that we're tracking hands in real space"},{"time":477000,"text":"becomes really important because we can reach in,"},{"time":480000,"text":"not in 2D, not in fake 2D, but in actual 3D."},{"time":482000,"text":"Here are some selection planes."},{"time":484000,"text":"And we'll perform this Boolean operation"},{"time":487000,"text":"because we really love yellow and tapirs on green grass."}]},{"cues":[{"time":499000,"text":"So, from there to the world of real work."},{"time":502000,"text":"Here's a logistics system,"},{"time":504000,"text":"a small piece of one that we're currently building."},{"time":506000,"text":"There're a lot of elements."},{"time":508000,"text":"And one thing that's very important is to combine traditional tabular data"},{"time":511000,"text":"with three-dimensional and geospatial information."},{"time":514000,"text":"So here's a familiar place."},{"time":517000,"text":"And we'll bring this back here for a second."},{"time":520000,"text":"Maybe select a little bit of that."},{"time":523000,"text":"And bring out this graph."},{"time":526000,"text":"And we should, now,"},{"time":528000,"text":"be able to fly in here"},{"time":531000,"text":"and have a closer look."},{"time":534000,"text":"These are logistics elements"},{"time":536000,"text":"that are scattered across the United States."}]},{"cues":[{"time":545000,"text":"One thing that three-dimensional interactions"},{"time":548000,"text":"and the general idea of imbuing"},{"time":550000,"text":"computation with space affords you"},{"time":552000,"text":"is a final destruction of that unfortunate"},{"time":554000,"text":"one-to-one pairing between human beings and computers."},{"time":557000,"text":"That's the old way, that's the old mantra:"},{"time":559000,"text":"one machine, one human, one mouse, one screen."},{"time":561000,"text":"Well, that doesn't really cut it anymore."},{"time":564000,"text":"In the real world, we have people who collaborate;"},{"time":567000,"text":"we have people who have to work together,"},{"time":570000,"text":"and we have many different displays."},{"time":573000,"text":"And we might want to look at these various images."},{"time":576000,"text":"We might want to ask for some help."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578000,"text":"The author of this new pointing device"},{"time":581000,"text":"is sitting over there,"},{"time":583000,"text":"so I can pull this from there to there."},{"time":585000,"text":"These are unrelated machines, right?"},{"time":588000,"text":"So the computation is space soluble and network soluble."},{"time":591000,"text":"So I'm going to leave that over there"},{"time":593000,"text":"because I have a question for Paul."},{"time":595000,"text":"Paul is the designer of this wand, and maybe its easiest"},{"time":597000,"text":"for him to come over here and tell me in person what's going on."},{"time":600000,"text":"So let me get some of these out of the way."},{"time":605000,"text":"Let's pull this apart:"},{"time":608000,"text":"I'll go ahead and explode it."},{"time":611000,"text":"Kevin, can you help?"},{"time":618000,"text":"Let me see if I can help us find the circuit board."},{"time":623000,"text":"Mind you, it's a sort of gratuitous field-stripping exercise,"},{"time":626000,"text":"but we do it in the lab all the time."},{"time":629000,"text":"All right."},{"time":631000,"text":"So collaborative work, whether it's immediately co-located"},{"time":634000,"text":"or distant and distinct, is always important."},{"time":637000,"text":"And again, that stuff"},{"time":639000,"text":"needs to be undertaken in the context of space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":644000,"text":"And finally, I'd like to leave you with a glimpse"},{"time":647000,"text":"that takes us back to the world of imagery."},{"time":649000,"text":"This is a system called TAMPER,"},{"time":651000,"text":"which is a slightly whimsical look"},{"time":653000,"text":"at what the future of editing"},{"time":655000,"text":"and media manipulation systems might be."},{"time":657000,"text":"We at Oblong believe that media should be"},{"time":659000,"text":"accessible in much more fine-grained form."},{"time":662000,"text":"So we have a large number of movies"},{"time":664000,"text":"stuck inside here."},{"time":666000,"text":"And let's just pick out a few elements."},{"time":669000,"text":"We can zip through them"},{"time":672000,"text":"as a possibility."},{"time":674000,"text":"We can grab elements off the front,"},{"time":676000,"text":"where upon they reanimate, come to life,"},{"time":679000,"text":"and drag them down onto the table here."},{"time":684000,"text":"We'll go over to Jacques Tati here"},{"time":687000,"text":"and grab our blue friend"},{"time":690000,"text":"and put him down on the table as well."},{"time":693000,"text":"We may need more than one."},{"time":698000,"text":"And we probably need,"},{"time":700000,"text":"well, we probably need a cowboy"},{"time":702000,"text":"to be quite honest."},{"time":704000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":706000,"text":"Yeah, let's"},{"time":709000,"text":"take that one."},{"time":711000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":713000,"text":"You see, cowboys and French farce people"},{"time":715000,"text":"don't go well together, and the system knows that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":720000,"text":"Let me leave with one final thought,"},{"time":722000,"text":"and that is that"},{"time":724000,"text":"one of the greatest English language writers"},{"time":726000,"text":"of the last three decades"},{"time":728000,"text":"suggested that great art is always a gift."},{"time":731000,"text":"And he wasn't talking about whether the novel costs 24.95 [dollars],"},{"time":734000,"text":"or whether you have to spring 70 million bucks"},{"time":736000,"text":"to buy the stolen Vermeer;"},{"time":738000,"text":"he was talking about the circumstances of its creation"},{"time":740000,"text":"and of its existence."},{"time":742000,"text":"And I think that it's time that we asked"},{"time":744000,"text":"for the same from technology."},{"time":746000,"text":"Technology is capable of"},{"time":748000,"text":"expressing and being imbued with"},{"time":751000,"text":"a certain generosity,"},{"time":753000,"text":"and we need to demand that, in fact."},{"time":755000,"text":"For some of this kind of technology,"},{"time":758000,"text":"ground center is"},{"time":761000,"text":"a combination of design, which is crucially important."},{"time":763000,"text":"We can't have advances in technology any longer"},{"time":766000,"text":"unless design is integrated from the very start."},{"time":769000,"text":"And, as well, as of efficacy, agency."},{"time":772000,"text":"We're, as human beings, the creatures that create,"},{"time":775000,"text":"and we should make sure that our machines aid us in that task"},{"time":778000,"text":"and are built in that same image."}]},{"cues":[{"time":781000,"text":"So I will leave you with that. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":783000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":798000,"text":"Chris Anderson: So to ask the obvious question --"},{"time":801000,"text":"actually this is from Bill Gates --"},{"time":803000,"text":"when? (John Underkoffler: When?)"},{"time":806000,"text":"CA: When real? When for us, not just in a lab and on a stage?"},{"time":810000,"text":"Can it be for every man, or is this just for corporations and movie producers?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":813000,"text":"JU: No, it has to be for every human being."},{"time":815000,"text":"That's our goal entirely."},{"time":817000,"text":"We won't have succeeded"},{"time":819000,"text":"unless we take that next big step."},{"time":821000,"text":"I mean it's been 25 years."},{"time":823000,"text":"Can there really be only one interface? There can't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825000,"text":"CA: But does that mean that, at your desk or in your home,"},{"time":827000,"text":"you need projectors, cameras?"},{"time":830000,"text":"You know, how can it work?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":832000,"text":"JU: No, this stuff will be built into the bezel of every display."},{"time":834000,"text":"It'll be built into architecture."},{"time":836000,"text":"The gloves go away in a matter of months or years."},{"time":839000,"text":"So this is the inevitability about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":841000,"text":"CA: So, in your mind, five years time,"},{"time":843000,"text":"someone can buy this as part of"},{"time":845000,"text":"a standard computer interface?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":847000,"text":"JU: I think in five years time when you buy a computer,"},{"time":850000,"text":"you'll get this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":852000,"text":"CA: Well that's cool."},{"time":854000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":858000,"text":"The world has a habit of surprising us as to how these things are actually used."},{"time":861000,"text":"What do you think, what in your mind is the first killer app for this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":864000,"text":"JU: That's a good question, and we ask ourselves that every day."},{"time":867000,"text":"At the moment, our early-adopter customers --"},{"time":870000,"text":"and these systems are deployed out in the real world --"},{"time":873000,"text":"do all the big data intensive, data heavy problems with it."},{"time":876000,"text":"So, whether it's logistics and supply chain management"},{"time":878000,"text":"or natural gas and resource extraction,"},{"time":881000,"text":"financial services, pharmaceuticals, bioinformatics,"},{"time":884000,"text":"those are the topics right now, but that's not a killer app."},{"time":886000,"text":"And I understand what you're asking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":888000,"text":"CA: C'mon, c'mon. Martial arts, games. C'mon."},{"time":890000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":892000,"text":"John, thank you for making science-fiction real."}]},{"cues":[{"time":895000,"text":"JU: It's been a great pleasure."},{"time":897000,"text":"Thank you to you all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":899000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}